 	HOW TO INSATLL LDV-ONLINE?

1. Install and configure mysql server and client
2. Start mysql server daemon: "sudo /etc/init.d/mysqld".";
3. Connect to db server as root like this: "mysql -u root ...".";
4. Create db for ldv-online: "CREATE DATABASE dbname".";
5. Create user for stats db: "CREATE USER 'dbuser'@'dbhost' 
   IDENTIFIED BY 'dbpass';".";
6. Add priviledges: "GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON dbname.* TO 
   'dbuser'@'dbhost' WITH GRANT OPTION;".";
7. Update privileges: "FLUSH PRIVILEGES;".";
8. Install apache2 web server with php5 module


9. Install server part of ldv-online: 
   - Create temp dir
   - Install ldv-online: prefix=/path/to/your/installation/directory \
        TMP_DIR=/path/to/tmpdir \
        WEB_DIR=/path/to/apahce/web/dir make install-online-server 

     (WEB_DIR in OpenSuSE by default: /srv/www/htdocs,
	      in Fedora: /var/www/html)
   - Write all parameters (dbname, dbhost, dbuser, dbpass) to 
     $prefix/ldv-online/confi/server.conf;
   - Configure your PATH: export PATH=$PATH:/$prefix/bin

10. Instal client part of ldv-online:
   - Create temp dir
   - Create dir for backend temp files: TMP_DIR/run
   - Copy 2.6.32.12 and 2.6.33.3 kernel sources to TMP_DIR/run
   - Install ldv online client:
          prefix=/path/to/your/installation/directory \ 
        TMP_DIR=/path/to/tmpdir \
        make install-online-node
   - Write all parameters (dbname, dbhost, dbuser, dbpass) to 
     $prefix/ldv-online/confi/client.conf;

11. Database and port options for client and server must be equals.
 
